                    <span>This is a wonderfully written, true story.  If you're a diver, especially on the east coast, you need to read this book.  My heart breaks everytime I read it.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Excellent Read</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>5</span>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Helpful: </span>
                      <span>0</span>
                      /
                      <span>0</span>
                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2005-04-11</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>As a beginning diver, I picked up this book while looking for some travel/diving guides. It was great read, as I didn't put it down until I was done.
<br />
<br />Superbly written to keep the readers attention, although the author, Bernie Chowdhury, went off on tangents every once in awhile, but not to the detrement of the story.
<br />
<br />The accounts and detail of the Rouse's technical diving in caves and wrecks, were wonderful. The history of underwater breathing apparatuses throughout the ages, was very interesting, especially for a uneducated beginner, such as myself.
<br />
<br />Accounts of nitrogen narcosis and decompression sickness (the bends), were vivid and enough to make a inexperienced diver such as myself take notice, allthough I will not be diving deep deco technical dives, such as the one's described in the book. It makes you think...
<br />
<br />The book grabbed me right away, although the outcome was readily apparent from the title. This story could have been fiction, knowing that it was not, made it all the more interesting.
<br />
<br />The end was riveting and tramatic, allthough I knew the outcome of the Rouse's. What saddened me most was that almost all the people in the book ultimately meet their end or have serious medical conditions that may or may not be attributed to their deep dives.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Must read for serious divers</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>5</span>
